-{"id":"frankenredis-4upy","title":"fr-runtime: CLIENT LIST output diverges from upstream Redis 7.2 (missing argv-mem/multi-mem/rbs/rbp/redir, extra watch, flags position)","description":"fr-runtime's CLIENT LIST output diverges from upstream Redis 7.2 in several ways: (1) MISSING fields: argv-mem (input argv memory), multi-mem (queued MULTI memory), rbs (read-buffer size), rbp (read-buffer position), redir (CLIENT TRACKING REDIRECT target id, default -1). (2) EXTRA field: watch=N (count of WATCHed keys) — Redis 7.2 dropped this field. (3) FIELD ORDER: fr emits flags=N at the very end; Redis 7.2 emits flags right after idle, before db. (4) lib-name / lib-ver order: Redis emits these AFTER resp; fr emits before. (5) fd is hardcoded to 0 vs Redis's actual epoll fd — minor but a real divergence; tools that grep on fd=N may misbehave.\n\nAcceptance: a fresh fr-server with one connected client emits CLIENT LIST in a single line whose tokens (and order) match upstream Redis 7.2's CLIENT LIST output for an equivalent client, modulo the fd field (fd=0 stays since fr doesn't track real fds for clients) and the per-instance values (id, addr port, qbuf, qbuf-free, tot-mem). Tools like redis_exporter that parse the line on field names (regex) will match. The conformance harness's CLIENT LIST live-oracle test gains a side-by-side text diff that asserts identical token ordering.\n\nReference: ran 'CLIENT LIST' against fr (port 16500) and vendored redis 7.2.4 (port 16501) with the same shape of single connected redis-cli client. fr line: 'id=2 addr=... laddr=... fd=0 name= age=0 idle=0 db=0 sub=0 psub=0 ssub=0 multi=-1 watch=0 qbuf=0 qbuf-free=0 obl=0 oll=0 omem=0 tot-mem=0 events=r cmd=client|list user=default lib-name= lib-ver= resp=2 flags=N'. Redis line: 'id=3 addr=... laddr=... fd=7 name= age=0 idle=0 flags=N db=0 sub=0 psub=0 ssub=0 multi=-1 qbuf=26 qbuf-free=20448 argv-mem=10 multi-mem=0 rbs=16384 rbp=16384 obl=0 oll=0 omem=0 tot-mem=37786 events=r cmd=client|list user=default redir=-1 resp=2 lib-name= lib-ver='.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-29T22:08:17.262396364Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-29T22:08:17.262396364Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id": "frankenredis-4upy", "title": "fr-runtime: CLIENT LIST output diverges from upstream Redis 7.2 (missing argv-mem/multi-mem/rbs/rbp/redir, extra watch, flags position)", "description": "fr-runtime's CLIENT LIST output diverges from upstream Redis 7.2 in several ways: (1) MISSING fields: argv-mem (input argv memory), multi-mem (queued MULTI memory), rbs (read-buffer size), rbp (read-buffer position), redir (CLIENT TRACKING REDIRECT target id, default -1). (2) EXTRA field: watch=N (count of WATCHed keys) — Redis 7.2 dropped this field. (3) FIELD ORDER: fr emits flags=N at the very end; Redis 7.2 emits flags right after idle, before db. (4) lib-name / lib-ver order: Redis emits these AFTER resp; fr emits before. (5) fd is hardcoded to 0 vs Redis's actual epoll fd — minor but a real divergence; tools that grep on fd=N may misbehave.\n\nAcceptance: a fresh fr-server with one connected client emits CLIENT LIST in a single line whose tokens (and order) match upstream Redis 7.2's CLIENT LIST output for an equivalent client, modulo the fd field (fd=0 stays since fr doesn't track real fds for clients) and the per-instance values (id, addr port, qbuf, qbuf-free, tot-mem). Tools like redis_exporter that parse the line on field names (regex) will match. The conformance harness's CLIENT LIST live-oracle test gains a side-by-side text diff that asserts identical token ordering.\n\nReference: ran 'CLIENT LIST' against fr (port 16500) and vendored redis 7.2.4 (port 16501) with the same shape of single connected redis-cli client. fr line: 'id=2 addr=... laddr=... fd=0 name= age=0 idle=0 db=0 sub=0 psub=0 ssub=0 multi=-1 watch=0 qbuf=0 qbuf-free=0 obl=0 oll=0 omem=0 tot-mem=0 events=r cmd=client|list user=default lib-name= lib-ver= resp=2 flags=N'. Redis line: 'id=3 addr=... laddr=... fd=7 name= age=0 idle=0 flags=N db=0 sub=0 psub=0 ssub=0 multi=-1 qbuf=26 qbuf-free=20448 argv-mem=10 multi-mem=0 rbs=16384 rbp=16384 obl=0 oll=0 omem=0 tot-mem=37786 events=r cmd=client|list user=default redir=-1 resp=2 lib-name= lib-ver='.", "status": "closed", "priority": 2, "issue_type": "bug", "assignee": "cc_1", "created_at": "2026-04-29T22:08:17.262396364Z", "created_by": "ubuntu", "updated_at": "2026-04-30T02:30:29.370108Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "closed_at": "2026-04-30T02:30:29.370108Z", "close_reason": "Both fr-runtime's client_info_line_for_session and fr-command's client_info_line now emit CLIENT LIST/INFO with upstream Redis 7.2 field order: id addr laddr fd name age idle flags db sub psub ssub multi qbuf qbuf-free argv-mem multi-mem rbs rbp obl oll omem tot-mem events cmd user redir resp lib-name lib-ver. Dropped watch=N (removed in 7.2), added redir + buffer-accounting fields (always 0 since fr doesn't track per-client buffers). Pinned by client_list_field_order_matches_upstream_redis_72 in fr-runtime. Shipped in 057c446."}
 {"id": "frankenredis-4x9a", "title": "redis parity: runtime EVAL BGREWRITEAOF regression should expect NOSCRIPT", "description": "Full fr-runtime runs are still red on eval_bgrewriteaof_rewrites_aof_snapshot because command parity now rejects BGREWRITEAOF from Lua with NOSCRIPT, but the runtime regression still expects the old success reply. Update the runtime expectation to the Redis-aligned NOSCRIPT surface and verify through rch.", "status": "closed", "priority": 2, "issue_type": "task", "created_at": "2026-04-21T18:50:31.754862465Z", "created_by": "ubuntu", "updated_at": "2026-04-21T18:54:47.075307402Z", "closed_at": "2026-04-21T18:54:47.072900897Z", "close_reason": "Completed", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
